parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid propulsion system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Check Hybrid System" light comes on
the vehicle loses power
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's lights and accessories may not function
the vehicle may not start
and the dashboard lights may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes do not respond properly
and the ABS light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rodent damage to wiring can cause electrical system failures, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical systems may malfunction
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving.
symptoms: The air conditioning system does not cool properly
and a moldy smell comes from the vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the push start ignition system can cause the engine to turn on unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine turns on unexpectedly
and the power button is lit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The visibility issues with the instrument panel can cause distraction and discomfort while driving.
symptoms: The gauges on the instrument panel are difficult to view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The optical distortion on the windshield can cause distraction and discomfort while driving.
symptoms: Point sources of light are duplicated or triplicated at distances through the front windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to increased stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
and there may be a hissing or whirring sound coming from the brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to increased stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
and there may be a hissing or whirring sound coming from the brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to increased stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
and there may be a hissing or whirring sound coming from the brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shut down of the hybrid power system can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or loses power
warning lights and messages appear on the dashboard
the vehicle can be driven but with reduced power
or the hybrid system shuts down completely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the inverter/converter can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Error code P0A94
message to pull over
loss of power
warning lights and messages appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: ABS
traction control
and brake light go on
error codes 16-17

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission/clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle rolls backward on a slope.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The mold/mildew smell can cause discomfort and health issues for the occupants.
symptoms: Musty smell from the vents
condenser clogged smell
unbearable to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of certain safety features can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Request for back-up cameras and auto braking as standard features.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to notify and repair the Takata recall can increase the risk of a crash or injury.
symptoms: Dealer failed to notify and repair the Takata recall.
